p: We used these testosterone ranges to assign sex to turtles not laparoscoped (N = 901), resulting in 668 females, 220 males and 13 unknowns with a sex ratio of 3.0F:1.0M ( Fig 2B). We did not find a significant change in sex ratios (% females) among years (χ 2 = 8.3, df = 9, P >0.5; Table 1, Fig 3) or size classes (χ 2 = 6.3, df = 7, P > 0.5; Table 2).
